        <num>CC 1877</num>
        <heading>1877.  Fortuitous event that has made performance impossible in part</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1877.  Fortuitous event that has made performance impossible in part
When a fortuitous event has made a party's performance impossible in part, the court may reduce the other party's counterperformance proportionally, or, according to the circumstances, may declare the contract dissolved.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109120</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
